title: Rwanda Imports
description: Imports in Rwanda increased to 533.91 USD Million in September from 493.49 USD Million in August of 2022. Imports in Rwanda averaged 295.32 USD Million from 1998 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 1859 USD Million in December of 2012 and a record low of 156.90 USD Million in October of 2016. Rwanda imports mainly food products, machinery and equipment, construction materials, petroleum products and fertilizers. Main imports partners are Kenya, Germany, Uganda and Belgium. This page provides - Rwanda Imports - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: National Institute of Statistics of Rwanda
